</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,152,951]" pageId="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,275,615,641]" pageId="40">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gagne" authorityYear="1981" box="[286,501,616,641]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Trichonta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[286,501,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="40">Trichonta pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<specimenCount box="[757,867,616,642]" pageId="40" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[944,1032,616,642]" name="Canada" pageId="40">Canada</collectingCountry>
and four British males, the latter being in the author’s collection and these having posterior setae on the hind tibia, although some more recent British material has these setae sparse or absent. It has only otherwise been recorded from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1250,1436,693,719]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="40">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sevcik, J." box="[159,312,731,758]" pageId="40" pagination="159 - 169" refId="ref45101" refString="Sevcik, J. (2001) New records of Diadocidiidae, Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae (Diptera: Sciaroidea) from the Czech Republic. C asopis Slezskeho Zemskeho Muzea, Opava (Serie A), 50, 159 - 169." type="journal article" year="2001">Ševčík 2001</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[381,485,732,758]" name="Hungary" pageId="40">Hungary</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sevcik, J. &amp; Papp, L." box="[503,759,731,758]" pageId="40" pagination="149 - 156" refId="ref45212" refString="Sevcik, J. &amp; Papp, L. (2002) Mycetophilidae (Diptera): additions and corrections to the &quot; Checklist of the Diptera of Hungary &quot;. Folia Entomologica Hungarica, 63, 149 - 156." type="journal article" year="2002">Ševčík &amp; Papp 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Because they lack posterior setae on the hind tibia the Sardinian specimens run to couplet 
<quantity box="[580,641,770,796]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4478" pageId="40" unit="in" value="57.0">57 in</quantity>
the key by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gagne, R. J." box="[783,950,770,796]" pageId="40" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref43024" refString="Gagne, R. J. (1981) A Monograph of Trichonta with a Model for the Distribution of Holarctic Mycetophilidae (Diptera). Technical Bulletin. United States Department of Agriculture, 1638, 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="1981">Gagné (1981)</bibRefCitation>
, where they agree with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Meigen, 1830)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Trichonta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitta">
<emphasis box="[1237,1320,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="40">T. vitta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Meigen, J. W." pageId="40" pagination="1 - 401" refId="ref44616" refString="Meigen, J. W. (1830) Systematische Beschreibung der bekannten europaischen zweiflugeligen Insekten. Hamm, 6, xi + 1 - 401 pp." type="book chapter" year="1830">Meigen, 1830</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having Sc ending free but have the dorsal part of the gonostylus short. The specimens are also described and figured here because fig. 119 of 
<bibRefCitation author="Gagne, R. J." box="[693,855,848,874]" pageId="40" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref43024" refString="Gagne, R. J. (1981) A Monograph of Trichonta with a Model for the Distribution of Holarctic Mycetophilidae (Diptera). Technical Bulletin. United States Department of Agriculture, 1638, 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="1981">Gagné (1981)</bibRefCitation>
shows the gonocoxites as having a simple margin and it is not apparent that this species has a medial excavation of the gonocoxites resembling that in 
<taxonomicName authority="Johannsen, 1912" authorityName="Johannsen" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Trichonta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patens">
<emphasis box="[1330,1436,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="40">T. patens</emphasis>
Johannsen, 1912
</taxonomicName>
. However, all parts of the gonostylus differ in structure from that species.
</paragraph>
